http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/%E2%80%98Cultural-pilgrimage%E2%80%99-in-city-tomorrow/article13978214.ece

A cultural pilgrimage taken out by Thapasya Kala Sahithya Vedi to spread the message ‘My land, My language, My culture,’ will visit various cultural centres in the city on January 4 and 5. The pilgrimage will start from Kanyakumari on Sunday and end at Gokarna on January 18.The pilgrimage will be led by prominent personalities such as Akkitham, S. Ramesan Nair, M.A. Krishnan, Thuravoor Visvambharan, P. Narayanakurup, Mankombu Gopalakrishnan, Madambu Kunjukuttan, N.K. Desam, music director Rajamani, P.G. Haridas, and C.G. Raj Gopal.The yatra will be given reception at 250 centres in the State. It will reach Kaliyikkavila on Monday and will have a stopover at Parassala Mahadevar Temple, C.V.R. Puram, Abhedananda Ashram, before reaching Neyyattinkara on the same day.On the next day, the pilgrimage will reach Kowdiar around 1 p.m. It will visit cultural centres here.